Functional-Requirement.name: Seperate Public and Goverment Access
Functional-Requirement.text: Two access points are required, one for the public to do business with SHPO and one for Government users to request operational roles, monitor, perform review and approval tasks, administrative tasks.

Functional-Requirement.name: Automatic Logout
Functional-Requirement.text: Actors accessing or attempting to access screen without out the proper role will automatically be logged out.

Functional-Requirement.name: Restrict Navigation
Functional-Requirement.text: Navication will be restricted to those actors with proper roles.

Functional-Requirement.name: Restrict Component Visibility
Functional-Requirement.text: Screen component should be resticted to those with proper roles.

Functional-Requirement.name: Login
Functional-Requirement.text: Login require an email addresss and password

Functional-Requirement.name: Email Identity
Functional-Requirement.text: users must be identifiable to the system by their email address

Functional-Requirement.name: Role Request by User
Functional-Requirement.text: Each Role must have a method (screen, button, or other) to request access from the administrator.

Functional-Requirement.name: Role Request Point of Access
Functional-Requirement.text: Role requests are limited by access point. The public access point will only accept requests for national register and environmental review access.

Functional-Requirement.name: Role Dependent Display
Functional-Requirement.text: Screens should have different displays based on the roles of registrant

Functional-Requirement.name: Roles are Additive
Functional-Requirement.text: Roles should be additive. As you gain roles you gain access to different parts of the system.

Functional-Requirement.name: Voluntary Notification
Functional-Requirement.text: Actors may request to be notified of changes made by other actors.
